  "prompt": "What are div1 and div2 on topcoder?",
  "response": "On Topcoder, \"Div1\" and \"Div2\" refer to divisions that categorize competitors based on their skill levels. This system allows for more balanced competitions and ensures participants face opponents with similar skill levels.\n\n1. **Division 1 (Div1):** This division consists of the more advanced and experienced competitors. Typically, a coder is placed in Div1 if their rating is above a certain threshold, commonly around 1200 or 1500 points, though this can vary over time and competition.\n\n2. **Division 2 (Div2):** This division is intended for less experienced competitors or those who are still improving their skills. Participants with a rating below the Div1 threshold are placed in Div2.\n\nTopcoder regularly hosts Single Round Matches (SRMs), and participants compete within their respective divisions. The problem sets for Div1 and Div2 are usually different, reflecting the varying difficulty levels appropriate to each group's skill level. As participants improve and their ratings increase, they can move from Div2 to Div1.",
